ide->pycharm

shortcuts

- Ctrl + j: auto-completion for templates/coding tasks, e.g. if __name__ = ...
- Ctrl + shift + F10: run
- Ctrl + x: delete line
- Ctrl + d: copy line to next line
- Ctrl + q: quick documentation
- Ctrl + Shift + i: quick definition
- Ctrl + f: find phrase in file
- Ctrl + r: replace phrase
- Ctrl + Alt + l: reformat code
- Ctrl + Alt + m: create new method by extracting code
- Alt + Enter: open context menu for creating getters, setters, main automatically
- Ctrl + Shift + k: comment/uncomment line(s) (customized)
- Shift + Esc: close tabs below like python console
- Shift + Tab: go to 'Switcher' to switch to another section

- Don't name files as "test" (testfile) or modules name
